Description: Rim and floor sherd of pottery plate with probable turn to foot; rounded lip with sharp moulding to its inside; brown clay; black glazed inside; ivy wreath frieze in added white inside; lip wholly glazed, messy glaze on underside.
Curator's comments: Neither Attic nor South Italian. 'Naukratis first season' written in pencil.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (ID.017)
